- To nudge the discussion towards a specific solution, you could ask, &#039;*Wouldn&#039;t* a phased implementation plan address your *concerns* about initial costs?&#039;
- You might ask, &#039;*Considering* the long-term benefits of this partnership, would a slightly higher initial investment be a *viable* option for your company?&#039;&quot;
- Instead of asking &#039;Is price your main concern?&#039;, ask &#039;What *factors* are most important to you in reaching a final agreement?&#039;&quot;
- To confirm a deadline, you could ask, &#039;So, we&#039;re both in *agreement* that the final decision needs to be made by next Friday, correct?&#039;&quot;

- &quot;Independent studies show that our training program can *increase* employee *productivity* by an average of 15% within the first quarter.&quot;
- &quot;*Implementing* our new software system won&#039;t just save you money; it will *also* streamline your workflow and improve *efficiency*.&quot;
- &quot;We understand you might be *concerned* about the initial investment. However, we can offer a *flexible* payment plan to make it more manageable for your *budget*.&quot;
